ace for assigning a block to a region, and for controlling the order of blocks within regions.','none'),(2332,'','default','Although blocks are usually generated automatically by modules (like the <em>User login</em> block, for example), administrators can also define custom blocks. Custom blocks have a title, description, and body. The body of the block can be as long as necessary, and can contain content supported by any available <a href=\"@input-format\">input format</a>.','none'),(2333,'','default','When working with blocks, remember that:','none'),(2334,'','default','since not all themes implement the same regions, or display regions in the same way, blocks are positioned on a per-theme basis.','none'),(2335,'','default','disabled blocks, or blocks not in a region, are never shown.','none'),(2336,'','default','when throttle module is enabled, throttled blocks (blocks with the <em>Throttle</em> checkbox selected) are hidden during high server loads.','none'),(2337,'','default','blocks can be configured to be visible only on certain pages.','none'),(2338,'','default','blocks can be configured to be visible only when specific conditions are true.','none'),(2339,'','default','blocks can be configured to be visible only for certain user roles.','none'),(2340,'','default','when allowed by an administrator, specific blocks may be enabled or disabled on a per-user basis using the <em>My account</em> page.','none'),(2341,'','default','some dynamic blocks, such as those generated by modules, will be displayed only on certain pages.','none'),(2342,'','default','For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@block\">Block module</a>.','none'),(2343,'','default','This page provides a drag-and-drop interface for assigning a block to a region, and for controlling the order of blocks within regions. To change the region or order of a block, grab a drag-and-drop handle under the <em>Block</em> column and drag the block to a new location in the list. (Grab a